The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 October is 4,822 (558.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 October, there were 435 new confirmed cases (50.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 October, there were 372 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 17% ( 63 extra cases).
